annotation.para:
It is important to remember that the accelleration rules should only be
                        used when the distance travelled by the characters over a {\bf short period}
                        of time is important

section.para:
In any physical targeted action there is the potential to specify the
                            \index{Attacks!Called Shots} \index{Called Shots} location of the
                            strike. That of course entails DF modifiers to the action. \index{}

Shock is the state brought on by massive disruption of the senses or
                            nervous system of the character. Shock effects range from the minor
                            (startled) to the major (being unconscious). \index{Damage!Shock}
